The paper presents a method for efficient learning of control policies for multiple related robotic motor skills, which involves training a neural network policy and selectively splitting its weights based on a per-weight metric. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Robotics (cs.RO), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on three continuous motor skill learning problems in simulation, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
